**Version Used**: VS 18.0.0 Insiders [11111.16]

**Steps to Reproduce**:
Invoke "Convert to LINQ" on the loop.

```csharp
class D
{
    public void M(IEnumerable<string> strings)
    {
        foreach (var x in Enumerable.Empty<string>())
        {
            bool b = true;
            A(); // A
            B(); // B
            P = 1; // P
            if (b)
            {
                C(); // C
                P = 3; // P
            }

            {
                P = 4; // P
            }
        }
    }

    void A() { }
    void B() { }
    void C() { }
    int P { get; set; }
}
```

**Expected Behavior**:
The whitespace between statement and comment is retained everywhere.

**Actual Behavior**:
The whitespace between statement and comment is lost, but only in the loop body directly. Any nested blocks are not affected.
```csharp
foreach (var b in from x in Enumerable.Empty<string>()
                    let b = true
                    select b)
{
    A();// A
    B();// B
    P = 1;// P
    if (b)
    {
        C(); // C
        P = 3; // P
    }

    {
        P = 4; // P
    }
}
```

